			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<br />
Purpose of role</p>
<p>
As a member of the Digital Studio a Senior Editor / mgfx designer will deliver award winning content across multiple accounts and R/GA internal. He / she will influence changes in consumer behaviour through ideas, creativity and the use of time-based media. You will make a difference to digital communications, marketing, advertising and inspire our clients and the company.</p>
<p>
The ideal candidate for the DS team is someone obsessive about the moving image &mdash; editing, animation, production and the latest video technologies. The candidate must be adept at taking ownership of editing assignments for web spots, branded content, short films, presentations and integrated video projects. They must also be an imaginative and conceptual designer with strong communication skills.</p>
<p>
<br />
Deliverables (criteria by which success can be measured)</p>
<p>
&bull; Deliver and inspire award-winning work from both him/ herself and others team members, influencing where appropriate a dramatic change through ideas, creativity and the use of interactive media.</p>
<p>
&bull; Consistently deliver a number of successful solutions and high quality work to clients on time.</p>
<p>
&bull; High-level internal and external client satisfaction.</p>
<p>
&bull; High level of team satisfaction.</p>
<p>
&bull; High level of accuracy and attention to detail.</p>
<p>
&bull; Learn new skills and stay up to date of technical and digital video developments and successfully apply these to work practices to help improve processes and procedures.</p>
<p>
&bull; Participate in a number of pitches.</p>
<p>
<br />
Responsibilities</p>
<p>
Concepting, Editing and Animation:</p>
<p>
&bull; Collaborate with creative directors, art directors, and writers developing stories for a variety of editorial projects.</p>
<p>
&bull; Help bring creative ideas to life in a relevant and engaging way, communicating ideas coherently and enthusiastically.</p>
<p>
&bull; Work closely with the line manager to drive clients forward, with proactive thinking and innovative ideas.</p>
<p>
&bull; Edit content for promo spots, scripted shorts, brand trailers, short-form documentaries, agency reels, and case studies.</p>
<p>
&bull; Seek approval and feedback from the line manager at the most appropriate points in the project in order to ensure a high quality of work.</p>
<p>
&bull; Play a key role in inspiring and motivating the client and other team members through the application of fresh and inventive motion work.</p>
<p>
&bull; Absorb creative direction while bringing unique ideas to the table.</p>
<p>
&bull; Demonstrate a strong sense of ownership and attention to detail during the production process.</p>
<p>
&bull; Provide feedback to and consultation with Creative Teams, Production teams and Client Services throughout the duration of the project.</p>
<p>
&bull; Regularly look for a way to incorporate emerging media and new media formats.</p>
<p>
&bull; Assist Studio team during video productions (camera operation, lighting, audio recording) </p>
<p>
&bull; Record and edit voiceover tracks</p>
<p>
&bull; Maintain edit suites for optimal editing workflow.</p>
<p>
&bull; Strong organizational and time management skills. Able to work on several deadlines at once.  </p>
<p>
&bull; Work independently and with teams.</p>
<p>
<br />
Management:</p>
<p>
&bull; Build good relationships with team members and ensure your team has a high level of morale.<br />
&bull; Identify team members training needs and be pro-active with support.<br />
&bull; Communicate client best practices and communicate it with junior members of the team.<br />
&bull; Ensure junior motion designers, editors and freelancers are meeting utilisation and billability targets.<br />
&bull; Identify recruitment needs and support the line manager in interviews for permanent or freelance positions.</p>
<p>
<br />
Qualification and experience</p>
<p>
<br />
&bull; Proven experience working as a Senior Editor is required.<br />
&bull; Experience working in a creative/agency environment is advantageous.<br />
&bull; A degree in Film, Animation, Visual Studies or other moving image-related field preferred.<br />
&bull; Proven creative success working with creative teams and Directors.<br />
&bull; Considerable experience executing creative, narrative and mixed format edits to a high standard<br />
&bull; Extensive experience using the most common software: FCP, Adobe Production Suite, Compression software<br />
&bull; Additional working knowledge and use of the following would be advantageous: Cinema 4D, one or more sound design tools.</p>
<p>
<br />
Key competencies</p>
<p>
<br />
&bull; Idea generation &ndash; the ability to consistently contribute new, innovative ideas that are on brand and on brief.</p>
<p>
&bull; Storyboarding and script development - a good understanding of best practice for pre-production.</p>
<p>
&bull; Good communication, planning, time-management and inter-personal skills</p>
<p>
&bull; Delegation &ndash; the ability to assess a broad range of tasks and determine which should be managed by oneself and which tasks should be passed to junior members of the team to manage, ensuring delivery is to the highest standards at all times.</p>
<p>
&bull; Mentoring &ndash; support and encourage team members and colleagues to manage their own learning in order that they continue to maximise their potential, develop their skills and improve their performance as part of an on-going process.</p>
<p>
Leadership attributes:</p>
<p>
&bull; Thinks strategically &ndash; knowledge of the Company&rsquo;s practices.<br />
&bull; Inspires creativity and innovation &ndash; imagines creative solutions.<br />
&bull; Drives results &ndash; achieves high levels of customer satisfaction.<br />
&bull; Builds teams &ndash; strengthens others through constructive feedback and mentoring.<br />
&bull; Exhibits professional excellence &ndash; demonstrates a strong sense of ownership.<br />
&bull; Builds relationships &ndash; takes a consultative approach.<br />
&bull; Communicates effectively &ndash; invites diverse points of view.<br />
&bull; Champions change &ndash; supports new initiatives.<br />
&nbsp;</p>
