R/GA is currently searching for a Human Resource Business Partner (HR Generalist) who will support designated internal departments by providing counsel and direction for leveraging talent around their business strategies. This role combines "hands-on" day-to-day operational human resources functions with strategic client advisory. The successful candidate must be able to operate in a fast-paced technologically and creatively driven environment.

Responsibilities:
 
-       Act as a strategic consultant to management, providing human resources expertise in implementing business initiatives and in determining the essential tactical human resource elements. Identify and frame human resources issues and solutions to business problems. Ensure the design and delivery of human resources products and services meet the needs of the business.
-       Act as advisor and coach to line managers on human resources issues such as managing change and supporting a positive work environment.
-       Participate in the development and implementation of human resources processes and programs, including but not limited to: assimilation of new employees, performance management, organizational development, employee recognition, learning and development and the annual talent and compensation review process.
-       Manage day-to-day operational aspect of human resources issues. Consult with managers on performance management (including performance issues and terminations, etc.), staffing plans and strategies, compensation plans and other issues. Counsel employees on various issues (performance issues and terminations, etc.) while maintaining employer advocacy role.
-       Counsel Managers and staff on development opportunities, career mobility and advancement, as well as performance management, organizational development, training, compensation, and programs to support corporate initiatives.
-       Strategize, communicate and market forward-thinking HR solutions and programs to help clients attract, retain and develop a diverse workforce.
-       Manage special projects as assigned, potentially including but not limited to: diversity strategy, corporate social responsibility, and talent management.
-       Partner with other HR Business Partners to ensure cross-utilization of information and projects.
 
 
Requirements:
 
