Senior Copywriter<br />
London<br />
<br />
<strong>Description</strong><br />
The Senior Copywriter is a copywriter who, after a proven period of success, is beginning to hone their instincts for what works and what does not. You not only recognize the importance of appraising and editing your own work, you are becoming skilled at it, as well. Your best ideas are not just creatively fresh but strategically sound and on brand, too. A Senior Copywriter is adept, or becoming adept, at speaking with clients and presenting copy and concepts to them, either in person or over the phone. Your colleagues trust her to act as a representative of the team and the work.<br />
&nbsp;<br />
A Senior Copywriter may be the only writer on a project, may be supervising a junior writer, or may be working side by side with other writers. In any case, you&nbsp;are expected to take responsibility for the quality of any copy writing deliverable ensuring that it meets R/GA standards for creative excellence and client satisfaction.&nbsp;<br />
&nbsp;<br />
A Senior Copywriter should possess the ability to work with clients in different industries and must be able to work comfortably with people from different creative disciplines and with different creative teams. You should also be able to collaborate effectively with producers, account managers, and others outside the immediate creative team (e.g., Digital Studio, production vendors).<br />
