The Plant Manager is responsible for the day to day management of the 4 Building, 150,000 square feet R/GA Campus. A firm knowledge of building mechanical system, including but not limited to HVAC, Electrical, Plumbing, Network Wiring as well as a general knowledge of building and construction trades is required. The Plant Manager is responsible for managing the facilities planning activities for R/GA"s NY campus by coordinating, supervising, assessing, planning, guiding and evaluating facilities design and remodeling projects to completion; coordinating and directing the custodial, grounds, maintenance programs, campus events, and energy management operations; supervising, training and evaluating the work of assigned personnel.  Analyzes needs for new and/or existing facilities and makes recommendation for facilities improvements; determines new and remodeled facilities project scope and timelines.

 

