			<description><![CDATA[General summary 
A Producer manages interactive projects from kick-off to delivery on time, on budget, and on brief. A Producer is everyone"s point person for the project. Clients and internal team members rely on you for everything they need to know about a project: what to expect, what to do next, and where they need to be.

Responsibilities 



Define the scope of projects (goals, deliverables, schedule, and budget) 

Lead and inspire teams by communicating a vision for the project as well as involving people at the optimal levels for project success and overall account utilization 

Manage interdisciplinary teams of visual designers, writers, interaction designers, and programmers helping to evolve creative concepts into clear sets of deliverables in a way that balances client requirements with team growth and morale 

Serve as the main client interface on projects, helping define vision, clarifying strategic requirements, explaining complex ideas clearly, and managing expectations 

Serve as primary day-to-day contact for clients 

Keep projects on track through clear task lists, issue tracking, status reports, and meeting notes 

Lead efficient meetings and conference calls with the ability to effectively setup the presentation of creative work 

Clearly communicate project issues and resolution to the client and internal team 

Play a dual role of client advocate and R/GA team advocate 

Be passionate about delivering the best creative, but find ways of producing it that does not jeopardize schedule and budget




Knowledge / Experience / Ability



Prior experience (2-4 years) as a interactive producer or directly related experience 

Experience developing project plans using MS Project 

Experience managing project budgets over $300,000 

Experience managing marketing, creative or technology projects 

Experience developing Statement of Work 

Experience managing clients (external or internal) on project scope and delivery 

Excellent communication skills, including presentation development and business writing 

Familiarity with web development technologies. Knowledge of software quality assurance process is desirable. 

Strong problem solving skills; responsive and flexible to evolving responsibilities and changing environment 

Bachelor's degree or equivalent required. PMI certification a plus. 




This position reports to the Executive Producer.

Compensation is commensurate with experience
 
Candidate must be legally authorized to work in the EU or have validation of eligibility to work in the EU to apply.


