<p>
<strong><u>R/GA London &ndash; Senior Interaction Designer&nbsp;</u></strong>At R/GA, Interaction Designers are integral to the creative process and play pivotal roles in the strategy, conception and design of groundbreaking multi-context platforms like Nike Plus, Nokia Vine, and NikeiD. We are seeking IDs of all levels who have experience connecting customers and brands through intuitive interfaces and trans-formative brand experiences. Preference will be given to people who demonstrate a combination of strategic, conceptual and design skills<br />
<br />
<strong>Description&nbsp;<br />
<br />
Key Objectives&nbsp;<br />
- To create interactive experiences which are useful to users and promote a business&rsquo;s product and brand&nbsp;<br />
- To understand and refine client strategy&nbsp;<br />
<br />
Responsibilities&nbsp;<br />
<br />
&bull; Requirement gathering &ndash; including stakeholder interviews, competitive research, technical feasibility assessments, design explorations, strategic analysis, and consensus building with the client.&nbsp;<br />
&bull; Concepting &ndash; coming up with the key ideas that drive a project and supporting ideas needed to implement them in various channels (TV, print, mobile, in-store, web, out-of-home, etc.). Senior Interaction Designer deliverables include: prototypes, proof of concept documents, wire frames, user flows, use cases, user scenarios.&nbsp;<br />
&bull; Experience Documents &ndash; includes, site maps, logic flows, wireframes, functional specifications, data models parameters, prototypes, keyframes.&nbsp;<br />
&bull; Presentations &ndash; throughout the process, interaction designers must present various aspects of the user experience to the development team, clients and stakeholders.&nbsp;<br />
&bull; Quality Assurance &ndash; during development, interaction designers&rsquo; track and monitor progress on development and quality of the user experience. This often involves revising experience documents.&nbsp;<br />
<br />
<br />
Knowledge, skills &amp; experience required&nbsp;<br />
&bull; Proven successful actual design experience in an interactive agency&nbsp;<br />
&bull; Strong understanding of interactive experiences, channels, and design principles&nbsp;<br />
&bull; Proficiency in underlying interactive technologies such as web and mobile&nbsp;<br />
