			<description><![CDATA[The creative director
 
A creative director is responsible for shaping the creative direction of the work that R/GA produces for a given client as part of a team of highly skilled and innovative multi disciplinary people
 
The creative director is responsible for ensuring that the work the team produces is in line with the client"s strategy and is appropriate to its brand.
 
In collaboration with the visual designers, interaction designers, and copywriters on a project, the creative director ensures that the quality of the concept and the work meets R/GA standards for creative excellence and client satisfaction.
 
The creative director should be R/GA"s point person in all interactions with a client where creative work is involved.
 
The creative director is the final arbiter of all disputes concerning creative work produced for a client and is responsible for providing a "united creative front" to the client.
 
The creative director, solely or in conjunction with senior members of the team is responsible for managing his/her department and ensuring that all administrative tasks are successfully performed.
 
The creative director should also work to mentor those in his/her department with a view toward fostering professional growth and commitment to R/GA.
 
Externally, a creative director must possess the ability to work with clients in different industries and handle different types of client relationships. Internally, a creative director must be able to work comfortably with people from different creative disciplines and with different creative teams. Within this role, the Creative Director, will be largely responsible for shaping the comms and campaigns output for London, working with top 5 global Brand' s and many more interesting clients. Working tightly with the team, complimenting them, and also adding invaluable creative input gained from years experience at the top of their game. This experience can come from top global ATL agencies, or indeed digital industry leaders, but the focus here is on building experiential digital campaigns that seamlessly work as part of a multi platform offering, engaging people from all over the world. The expectation will be to have the proven ability to think outside of the banner and micro site trends, if needs be and demonstrate how using all technology available, you can engage people and immerse them in rich and creative experiences.
 
Candidates must be eligible to work in the EU.
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
