R/GA Media Group, Inc. (www.rga.com) seeks an experienced International Business Operations Director to oversee the company"s rapidly expanding international offices.

Summary

This is an executive position responsible for business operations oversight of R/GA"s international (outside the US) offices. R/GA currently has 6 international offices, with additional locations planned for 2011, 2012, and beyond.

The position is a critical connection point between the senior-most executives in the company and the individual offices. Candidates must have the ability to partner effectively with the individual office MDs while also implementing global practices and policies which support the company"s integrated, cross-office model. The position will be partnered with an International Creative Director.

International business experience is essential, as is experience in digital marketing, design, and/or product development. Digital agency experience is highly preferred.

The position will be based in London, with significant travel to NYC HQ and to individual international offices. It reports to the company Chief Operating Officer, with a "dotted line" to the company"s Chief Executive Officer. The individual in this position will be a member of the R/GA executive management team.

Responsibilities

Working with Executive Team:



work with COO, CFO, and exec team to evolve best practices for internal business models and processes

provide coordination between NYC HQ and international offices

assist in creation of domestic or foreign corporate entities to expand global reach

ensure that R/GA maintains full legal compliance while optimizing business opportunities by keeping abreast of legal, tax, financial, HR, banking, and other policy issues in territories where offices are located (with the help of local accountants and/or attorneys)

ensure consistency of business operational processes and procedures between individual international offices according to company policies and direction from CEO, COO, and CFO

participate in overall company strategic planning

drive international new business efforts as directed by company executive team

weekly update to CEO and exec mgmt

monthly P&L reporting to COO and CFO

serve as "eyes and ears" on the ground

engage with IPG corporate or sister-company resources as need to achieve R/GA objectives

represent R/GA at international industry events





Working with individual office Managing Directors:



enable inter-office collaboration between client teams and offices according to R/GA"s integrated model

support office MDs with regard to day-to-day operational issues

anticipate, identify, and troubleshoot issues on a proactive basis and implement plans to resolve

work with office MDs to develop and present annual budget plans and quarterly updates to CFO and COO

regularly review financial performance of client accounts in each international office, develop strategies for improvement, and escalate issues to company COO, CFO, and CEO

identify and assess opportunities to grow business within individual office territories with new and existing clients, particularly existing global clients

assess potential business partners and suppliers within individual office territories





Qualifications:



10+ years of international business experience

10+ years of agency management experience

5+ years of digital marketing, design, product development experience

significant experience with legal, tax, corporate, HR issues in multiple territories

significant experience developing strategic and operational plans

broad financial and operational management expertise

proven ability to align individual international offices with overall company objectives

ability to understand nuances of individual office cultures

ability to work in a fast-paced, constantly evolving entrepreneurial environment

willingness and availability for significant travel

multi-lingual speakers preferred






