			<description><![CDATA[R/GA
Director, Resource Management

Job Description
R/GA is searching for a Director, Resource Management to manage a team of Group Resource Managers who are responsible for increasing efficiency across all agency client teams through effective staff bandwidth allocation. This person will fill an essential role in daily company operations through oversight of staff aggregate bandwidth, utilization and realization rates, retention/employee relations issues, and ongoing matching of individual project needs with staff skill sets. Development of a nuanced understanding of creative and technical talents of numerous individual staff members will be critical, as well as an ability to serve as a sounding-board and source of confidence within a fast-paced group setting. This position reports to the Chief Operating Officer.

Duties and Responsibilities



Track staffing trends, including rotations on and off accounts, hires and departures, FTE count and headcount across all accounts with an overall view of resourcing trends in the agency.

Work to solve problems by facilitating conversations between key players, as well as by coming up with creative solutions for those issues.

Run weekly utilization reports and escalate information that informs opportunities to increase operational efficiencies within the agency.

Maintain an understanding of the workflow and staffing needs in all R/GA offices to facilitate resource-sharing between offices; function as a liaison of information to support collaboration between offices.

Provide a point of escalation for the Group Resource Managers and client team leads regarding account resourcing issues.

Function as the team representative within the Agency through direct communication with Chief Operating Officer, Office Heads, Department Heads, and Client Team Leads.

Provide leadership to the Group Resource Management team by enhancing group best practices.

Communicate relevant strategic initiatives across the agency to the Group Resource Managers.

Understand skill sets of all company creative and technology resources in order to support Group Resource Managers as they provide solutions to staffing issues.

Work alongside the Group Resource Managers to reinforce intra-group resource sharing.

Serve as "eyes and ears" for Chief Operating Officer with regard to staffing, efficiency, productivity, and other issues across the agency.

Partner with Director of Recruitment to identify priorities regarding potential hiring needs.

Articulate and support career path development for the Group Resource Managers.

Assist in retention of key talent as needed.

Special projects assigned by COO, as needed.




Requirements



Knowledge of digital media industry required

8-10 years of creative management, project management, traffic, or operations experience within an agency environment; 3-5 years managing direct reports.

Strong knowledge of operations and workflow within an advertising agency

Experience with inter-office collaboration processes, including in an international context

Nuanced understanding of core disciplines within a digital agency, such as Interaction Design, Visual Design, Copy, Programming, Mobile, Social, etc.

Familiarity with extended capabilities of a digital agency, such as live-action video production, CG/animation, application software development, digital advertising development, etc.

Adept at modeling data into meaningful action items.

Must have excellent interpersonal skills, superior written and verbal communication 

Must work collaboratively to develop staffing solutions 

Quick, creative problem solver

Work well under pressure; detail-oriented; self-motivated; organized

Some budgeting experience in Production a plus

Possess strong command of databases and MS Excel, and familiarity with enterprise management applications

MBA preferred


