The primary role of the Desktop Support Administrator is to provide IT technical support to R/GA employees via remote tools, deskside support, email and over the phone. This second level support position is responsible for the intake of IT issues and requests and opening tickets and troubleshooting in the following technologies; PC and Macintosh desktops, laptops, peripherals, software, operating systems, email applications, network connectivity, printing services and mobility devices. Must be proficient in trouble-shooting hardware, network and printing issues. Fluent with OS X, 10.6 and Windows 7.
 
