The Visual Designer, Data Visualization makes design decisions and visually quantifies ideas by independently creating digital data eco systems. S/he contributes multiple ideas and solutions that reflect an awareness of the overall client and marketing goals, as well as an understanding of the target audience. This position creates interfaces/design solutions that make data useful, accessible, and meaningful by working collaboratively with the statistics and technology leads through rapid prototyping cycles.
 
 
Key Responsibilities:
 




Defines the visual design of digital data eco system by incorporating expert understanding of the target audience.

Creates interesting and legible interfaces/design solutions that make data useful and accessible.

Makes design decisions and visually quantifies ideas that reflect a versatile range of ideas and deep understanding of the mediums used.

Works collaboratively with a multidisciplinary team to build useful, well-designed interactive graphics and experiences.

Independently creates and executes highly polished visual design that is consistently on brand and directly connects to solving the client's business needs.

Builds useful interactive experiences through rapid and interative prototyping cycles by being responsive and adapting quickly to changes.

Identifies appropriate tools/techniques to projects based on a familiarity with broad set of design tools and their applications. Demonstrates expert mastery of Adobe creative suite and presentation software, and is able to direct others in its best practices. Some literacy of programming languages.

