Participate in the development and implementation of human resources processes and programs, including but not limited to: assimilation of new employees, performance management, organizational development, employee recognition, learning and development through R/GA University and the annual talent and compensation review process.

Manage day-to-day operational aspect of human resources issues. Consult with managers on performance management (including performance issues, the grievance and disciplinary processes and terminations, etc.), staffing plans, key selection decisions and strategies, compensation plans and other issues. Counsel employees on various issues (performance issues and terminations, etc.) while maintaining employer advocacy role.

Counsel Managers and staff on development opportunities, career mobility and advancement, as well as performance management, organizational development, training, compensation, and programs to support corporate initiatives.

Strategize, communicate and market forward-thinking HR solutions and programs to help clients attract, retain and develop a diverse workforce.

Manage special projects as assigned, potentially including but not limited to: diversity strategy, corporate social responsibility, and talent management.

Partner with other HR Business Partners to ensure cross-utilization of information and projects.

Manage and facilitate the development and execution of internships departmentally.

Develop and manage HR reporting statistics as and when required by the VP, of Human Resources.

Accountability for other projects, locations will change dependent on business need and individual career plan.



 
Requirements:



10+ years of human resources generalist experience, including experience consulting with senior managers in a fast-paced, demanding and rapidly changing environment.  Experience working in a fast-paced technologically and creatively driven environment preferred.

5+ years of demonstrated strength in handling complex employee relations issues.

International experience required. Experience with dealing with International relocations a plus.

In-depth knowledge of Employment law is a requirement.

Be a client-focused, proactive team player.

Ability to use research methods effectively, including data collection, diagnostic, and analytical skills.

Bachelor's degree or equivalent experience. Masters preferred.

Strong technical human resources expertise (compensation, staffing, etc.) to support and educate line management as well as to develop best practices within the team.

Ability to think strategically, but influence and act tactically in a very "hands-on" way.

Experience with "hands-on" delivery of performance management, compensation planning, management coaching, and process improvement.

Demonstrated situational flexibility.

Experience managing projects including conceiving, designing and implementing these projects.

Effective at building credibility quickly and maintaining relationships with clients, employees and human resources partners. Ability to accomplish objectives through influence and persuasion.

Strong leadership skills.

Articulate, with excellent communication skills and the ability to frame problems and solutions quickly and concisely.

Familiarity with HR systems, preferably Peoplesoft; strong PC proficiency, especially Excel.

Language skills a plus.


