			<description><![CDATA[The junior copywriter is a copywriter in training. He is in the process of learning the copywriter"s craft&mdash;how to think conceptually, how to write engaging copy that ties back to strategic/business goals, how to collaborate effectively with other disciplines&mdash;and to develop the professional skills he will need to advance in his career, such as presentation  and client-management skills. And so the junior copywriter might be expected to do a little bit of everything.
 

Duties and responsibilities 



Perform just about any task associated with the creation of content, including research, product descriptions, and basic proofreading tasks.  

Start to concept and collaborate with creative team, including other copywriters, interaction designers, art directors, and programmers. 

Shadow senior colleagues as they present work to clients and adapt work based on feedback. 

Work with producers to ensure work is delivered on deadline and up to clients" and agency"s standards. 

Begin to get comfortable writing in multiple styles and for multiple formats. 




