R/GA develops award-winning digital strategies for the world"s leading companies and brands. Sounds like a lot of work, right? It is. This is why we need fresh perspectives like yours. We work in an environment that embraces collaboration across all disciplines and encourages people to explore beyond the boundaries that limit visionary ideas. We"re creating digital experiences for brands like Nike, Verizon, and Nokia that build communities and connect people globally. As an intern, you"ll work side-by-side with our industry"s brightest minds&mdash;receiving mentorship, training, and experience on real, live accounts. You"ll also take part in seminars, panels, barcamps, and projects that will connect you with the latest industry trends and information. In short, you won"t be bored. So if you"re passionate about mapping the digital landscape as it evolves; and aspire to become a best in class designer, copywriter, technologist, producer, data intelligence specialist, client services liaison, or strategic planner; please apply for an internship at R/GA. We"d love to hear from you.
 
Interaction Design Intern
At R/GA, Interaction Designers are integral to the creative process and play pivotal roles in the strategy, conception and design of groundbreaking multi-context platforms like Nike Plus, Nokia Vine, and NikeiD. We are seeking Interns to participate in the forming of experiences which  connect customers and brands through intuitive interfaces and trans-formative brand experiences. Preference will be given to people who demonstrate a combination of strategic, conceptual and design chops.
 
Responsibilities for Interaction Design Interns include:
 
    * Participate in the brainstorming of and creation of concepts for best-in-class user experiences
    * Translate abstract concepts into simple and elegant user interfaces
    * Create concept models, user interface sketches, and detailed schematics.
    * Work closely with fellow creatives and developers to ensure the solidity of design systems
 
Qualifications include:
- A solid understanding and demonstration of user centered design principles
- A good understanding of what types of experiences are made possible by current digital technologies
