			<description><![CDATA[R/GA
Group Resource Coordinator

Job Description
R/GA is looking to hire a Group Resource Coordinator who will be responsible for increasing efficiency across a group of accounts through effective management of staff resourcing. This person will fill an essential role in daily company operations through oversight of staff aggregate bandwidth, utilization and realization rates, retention/employee relations issues, ongoing matching of individual project needs with staff skill sets. Development of a nuanced understanding of creative and technical talents of numerous individual staff members will be critical, as well as an ability to serve as a sounding-board and source of confidence within a fast-paced group setting.

Duties and Responsibilities



Liaise with the Producers and Group Leads to communicate overarching team needs 

Escalate to the appropriate department stakeholder any information related to: group rotations, retention/employee relations, increase or decrease in workflow, and projected staffing needs 

Gain knowledge and understanding of group members and skill sets across Creative and Technology departments

Monitor Group bandwidth and maximize efficiency across team resources

Report to Group Discipline leads to solve short- and long-term staffing needs

Point of contact for Group discipline leads regarding resource management and staffing

Track current FTEs and project needs for future FTEs

Work with the Producer and the Group Lead to understand the funding that supports the resources for the Group

Create and traffic requisition forms

Point of contact for new hires coming into the Group

Facilitate and monitor staff rotations

Retention: Sounding board for all staff on the Group

Work closely with recruiters, coordinators and HR to ensure proper placement of internal and external resources

Special projects as assigned

Collaborate with Group leads to support Group Events

Monitor timesheets and to ensure accuracy and compliance

Responsible for the analysis of timesheets with regard to utilization, timeswipes, and efficiency

Organize and facilitate meetings with key Group leads regarding overall Group staff allocations

Responsible for logging Group allocations into company tracking system

Collaborate with other Group Coordinators on a daily and weekly basis for intra-group resource sharing

Responsible for maintaining and/or authoring the following documents, among others:

Open Positions sheet

Monthly FTE sheet &ndash; current and projected

Expected vs. Allocated / Timesheet breakdown 

Group staff charts

Seating charts





Requirements




Knowledge of digital media industry a plus

2-3 years of traffic or operations experience in a production environment 

Possess strong command of MS Excel and familiarity with enterprise management applications 

Must have excellent interpersonal skills 

Superior written and verbal communication 

Must work collaboratively to develop staffing solutions 

Quick, creative problem solver

Works well under pressure; detail oriented 

Self-motivated; organized

Some budgeting experience in Production a plus 

Basic knowledge of disciplines within a digital agency a strong plus (e.g., Flash, .net, After Effects, 3D-Motion, etc)


