			<description><![CDATA[Title: 
Experience Strategist (XS)
 
Department: 
Interaction Design.  Reports to Director of Experience Strategy
 
Mission: 
Experience Strategy is a practice created to enable client teams to identify opportunities to design and deliver meaningful innovations that enhance and further differentiate our clients" product and service offerings from the competition. This practice will grow R/GA"s strategic significance with our clients and further differentiate us for our competition; enabling growth and retention with existing clients, and the acquisition of new clients. The XS is responsible for executing R/GA"s competencies as outlined below.
 
Role: 
The XS uses a variety of research and analytic tools to uncover the needs, expectations, and behaviors of customers and then combines those insights with a systematic understanding of business goals, market environment, and organizational capabilities to create memorable products, services and brand experiences. This work requires building clear, actionable insights and frameworks for multi-channel engagement programs that will not only deliver value to customers, but also competitive advantage and profit.
 
Responsibilities: 
Design research



Evangelize and effectively employ design research resources and tools

Plan and lead design research efforts tailored to discover insights that guide design and innovation

Expose latent customer needs and unpack meaning from sometimes obscure and disparate findings



Design strategy



Lead the analysis and synthesis processes to develop a comprehensive understanding of multi-channel customer experience, distill the important insights and link them together in frameworks or principles for design

Deliver insights&mdash;verbally and visually&mdash;in a way that generates empathy and engagement from the client and creative team

Translate the insights and information drawn from research into an inspirational and useful foundation for multi-channel experience design that satisfies customers" wants, needs and expectations



Design prototyping



Simulate the experiences that customers will have with new offerings and make concepts tangible enough that clients buy-in, build and test

Help shape prototypes for evaluation and to structure user feedback sessions

Evaluate alternative paths forward, selecting the one with the right mix of risk and reward



Practice (business) development



Working with the DXS, help write agency POVs and case studies

Assist in new business pitches and special projects



 
 
 
 
