			<description><![CDATA[General Summary

As a member of the executive team, the Managing Director is charged with leading R/GA"s growth and expansion in Singapore and the Asia Pac Region. He/she has primary responsibility for the continued development of R/GA"s Singapore office as a regional hub, as well as generating growth in Asia Pac through new business development efforts. In addition, he/she will be charged with management of the office P/L as well as management of client relationships, staff oversight, and quality of work. He/she will report to the company CEO, will work closely with company COO and CFO in day-to-day management, and will function as a business partner to the company executive team in New York.

 

 

PRIMARY RESPONSIBILITIES AND DUTIES:



Expand growth of R/GA Singapore as a regional hub

Develop a vision for growth across Asia Pac

Drive revenue and top-line growth through the strategic targeting of profitable accounts and industry verticals in the region

Develop deep and lasting client relationships that build and contribute to the expansion of R/GA"s business in Asia Pac

Develop and refine a go-to-market strategy including value propositions, services, and solutions

Management of a creatively-led, multi-disciplinary, marketing services organization focused on digital marketing including interactive experiences, ecommerce/transactional applications, online advertising (brand-building and/or direct marketing), email/CRM, mobile marketing

Oversee and identify new areas of growth for existing global client relationships

Work closely day-to-day with company COO and CFO on operating and financial matters

Monitor overall performance against annual operating and profit targets

Ensure office compliance with company business procedures including contracts and revenue recognition

Collaborate with company department heads based in New York to ensure that R/GA Singapore leverages company best practices and thought leadership



 

 

