Description: 
R/GA is looking for an Executive Creative Director to our team.  The ECD is a proven leader, effective communicator and an exceptional motivator as well as a public face for the agency. The position provides leadership across channels and the opportunity to partner with senior leadership to push our clients as well as the teams that you are accountable for.

Key Responsibilities/Accountabilities:



The ECD sets and implements the overarching creative direction and vision for his/her account(s) and/or team(s) as well as bring proactive leadership to the entire agency.

The position provides leadership through building the vision and mission, as opposed to the Creative Director who helps define that vision and mission and handles the day to day responsibilities of the account.

Manages multiple projects, clients, and budgets within deadlines

Determines promotion, assignments, evaluations, and incentives for creative managers

Responsible for shaping a general direction of the work that R/GA produces for a given client.

Manages and helps ensure the growth of individuals on the team and in the creative departments.

Builds strong relationships with multi-levels of marketing clients. Assists clients with deepening their knowledge of interactive marketing



 
