Initiative: Has a self-starting nature and is comfortable working as the sole planner in an office with a multidisciplinary team.  

Curiosity: Has a naturally curious mind, loves to explore and nurture intellect; knows how to observe and identify patterns that identify trends and key insights early; knows how to ask the right questions (relevant) and quantity of questions necessary to uncover key information that can be made actionable. Probably an avid observer and follower of popular culture and societal trends

Creativity: Gets excited about the mission of R/GA as an agency for the Digital Age, especially in regards to the creative output. Thus, they must feel invested in the creative process from conceptual stage through execution. Passionate about finding new ways to be creative and interesting in all aspects of planning. 

Technology Forward: Has a passion for technology, tinkering under the hood, and enjoys being a sought after authority and the resource that others turn to for emerging media. Probably very engaged personally with technology (blogging / microblogging, content creation, etc.)

Communication: Excellent oral and written communication skills; a great presenter, an active listener with consultative capabilities. A skillful communicator in tough situations where striking a balance between being direct/forceful and diplomacy is necessary.

Action Oriented: Self-motivated and self-starting individual who can take limited direction and produce tangible results.



Other 
Candidate will travel regularly for client and inter-agency meetings. This travel will be within the home region and likely beyond as necessary.

 
