<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Requirement gathering &ndash; including stakeholder interviews, competitive research, technical feasibility assessments, design explorations, strategic analysis, and consensus building with the client.&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Concepting &ndash; coming up with the key ideas that drive a project and supporting ideas needed to implement them in various channels (TV, print, mobile, in-store, web, out-of-home, etc.). Senior Interaction Designer deliverables include: prototypes, proof of concept documents, wire frames, user flows, use cases, user scenarios.&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Experience Documents &ndash; includes, site maps, logic flows, wireframes, functional specifications, data models parameters, prototypes, keyframes.&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Presentations &ndash; throughout the process, interaction designers must present various aspects of the user experience to the development team, clients and stakeholders.&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Quality Assurance &ndash; during development, interaction designers&rsquo; track and monitor progress on development and quality of the user experience. This often involves revising experience documents.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
