This position is responsible for the overall financial oversight and assurance that agencies and/or business units are in compliance with IPG policy, GAAP and Sarbanes-Oxley requirements surrounding Revenue.&nbsp; This includes the timely and accurate closing and reporting of the revenue of all business units.<br />
<br />
The Revenue Controller will report to the Chief Financial Officer of R/GA.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Roles and Responsibilities</strong>:<br />
<br />
<strong>Statement of Work Financial Reviews/Approvals</strong></p>
<p>
<br />
Reviews all financial and financial related sections of Statements of Work, Project Change Notices and similar client contracts with regard to accuracy and revenue recognition items including but not limited to:</p>
<ul>
<li>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Langauge that may impact our ability to recognize revenue in a timely manner</li>
<li>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Mathematical accuracy in all areas</li>
<li>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Invoicing schedules</li>
<li>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Comparison to Reporter</li>
<li>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Ensures compliance with GAAP, Sarbanes-Oxley and IPG policy with regard to appropriate revenue recognition</li>
<li>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Acts as liaison with external auditors and IPG on revenue matters</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Master Service Agreement Reviews</strong></p>
<p>
To look at all areas of an MSA that can impact revenue recognition including but not limited to:</p>
<ul>
<li>
&nbsp;&nbsp; Termination language</li>
<li>
&nbsp;&nbsp; Acceptance clausesReporting</li>
<li>
&nbsp;&nbsp; Client audits</li>
<li>
&nbsp;&nbsp; Invoice &amp; Payment terms</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>&nbsp; Revenue Recognition</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Provides timely and accurate revenue recognition calculation and reporting to parent company in accordance with US GAAP and IPG SP&amp;P&rsquo;s for all R/GA companies</li>
<li>
Reviews all contracts and ensures proper revenue recognition in accordance with US GAAP and IPG SP&amp;P&rsquo;s</li>
<li>
Ensures that all Estimate to Complete confirmations for both retainer and incremental jobs are sent and responded to on a timely basis</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Rate Cards</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Develop annual recommendation for agency Standard Rate card based on predetermined calculations using current salaries, benefit rates, overhead and profit factors</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>
&nbsp;Develop and maintain client specific rate cards as might be required by contractual calculations</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>IPG Client Agreement application</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
&nbsp;This is the key client contract input tool used by IPG for auditing and approving revenue recognition methods based upon size of contracts. To that end this is a system that is critical to keep up to date and accurate</li>
</ul>
