The Assistant Media Planner/Buyer will work under the supervision of senior media staff and will perform media planning and buying activities such as the development, execution, maintenance, reporting and reconciliation of media plans across a number of key accounts. This position is expected to work in collaboration with supervisors to perform day-to-day activities for media buy stewardship. Moreover this person is expected to focus on problem resolution as required.</p>
<p>
<strong>Media Planning/Buying</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Implementing and managing bid-managed and publisher-negotiated campaigns across websites, search engines, DSPs and native ad platforms such as Facebook, LinkedIn and Twitter</li>
<li>
Assisting in the online media planning process by pulling rankers and leveraging other site measurement data</li>
<li>
Compiling research proposals, RFPs and media proposals</li>
<li>
Discovering key data to support planning and buying strategies</li>
<li>
Pulling general media research such as competitive data</li>
<li>
Evaluating the success of strategies and recommend ongoing enhancements</li>
<li>
Providing competitive insight and analysis</li>
<li>
Investigating new performance media opportunities and make recommendations</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Media Buy Stewardship</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Employ quality assurance principles to ensure campaigns are launched and operating as planned</li>
<li>
Develop and share a wealth of knowledge and best practice in planning and buying strategies</li>
<li>
Prepare, manage and issue insertion orders as well as review contracts with the media</li>
<li>
Interact with third-party ad servers to issue trafficking requirements, etc.</li>
<li>
Tracking, compiling, and analyzing data for negotiation and client reporting</li>
<li>
Billing reconciliation activities such as matching back invoices to insertion orders in order to reconcile</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Desired Skills &amp; Experience</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Experience an advantage but not required.</li>
<li>
Masters or higher in Economics, Psychology or Statistics</li>
<li>
Familiarity with media channels such as mobile, search, social, display, etc.</li>
<li>
Aptitude to work with syndicated and related online media research resources; prior experience will be given preference</li>
<li>
Possess solid math skills</li>
<li>
Be detailed an accurate in performing duties</li>
<li>
Ability to interact with third-party ad servers and rich-media technologies; prior experience in this area will be a plus</li>
<li>
Proficiency and fluency in basic office applications such as Excel, Powerpoint and Word</li>
<li>
Possess ability for strong written and oral presentation skills</li>
<li>
Education: BA/BS required</li>
</ul>
