We seek an accomplished design researcher/strategist to join our growing Product Innovation team. The successful candidate will possess a unique blend of skills, with primary strengths in design research and a proven history of crafting successful, insight-driven product development strategies.</p>
<p>
The Experience Strategist uses a variety of research and analytic tools to uncover the needs, expectations, and behaviors of customers and then combines those insights with a systematic understanding of how business goals, market environment, and organizational capabilities could be orchestrated to create and deliver memorable and meaningful products, services and brand experiences.</p>
<p>
The ideal candidate must have demonstrated experience guiding user research and synthesizing research insights to clarify opportunities for innovation, frame design problems and inform business strategies&mdash;particularly business strategies involving new products and services.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
This role requires excellent oral and visual communication, proficiency in a range of research methodologies, as well as analytical and creative thinking.&nbsp; The candidate must demonstrate strong leadership, personal initiative, and accountability while embracing a collaborative approach.</p>
<p>
Responsibilities and skills:</p>
<p>
<strong>Support the research and strategy development process</strong>. You will work with client(s), colleagues and partners to develop a deep understanding of the competitive landscape, the client&rsquo;s brand strategy and immersion into user needs. The successful candidate must drive product development by connecting design research to business strategy by:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Rapidly building expertise on new businesses and industry verticals</li>
<li>
Analyzing secondary research and analytics to identify key user, business and design trends, and to frame opportunities and research plans.</li>
<li>
Planning, recruiting and conducting primary user research</li>
<li>
Leading the synthesis process to develop cohesive, compelling strategic visions that can guide both design and business strategies.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Serve as your clients&rsquo; strategic partner and guide</strong>. Alongside client services and other colleagues, you will inspire and shepherd clients through the discovery, concepting and prototyping process, guiding them to compelling solutions that will delight customers and the organizational changes necessary to deliver and sustain them by:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Assessing client business models and operations with an understanding of their impact on the current product or service offerings and the related customer experience.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Collaborate with design teams</strong>. You will work with teams of designers, writers, technologists and fellow strategists to inform the product development process and bring amazing new experiences to market. Continuing iteration of design research and strategy is critical at every point in the product development process to ensure that we shape and craft the experiences we develop to be delightfully different and optimally effective in meeting client objectives by:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Working effectively in multi-disciplinary teams in high-pressure situations</li>
<li>
Delivering insights and frame opportunities&mdash;verbally and visually&mdash;in a way that generates empathy and engagement from the client and creative team.</li>
<li>
Collaborating closely to ensure that all project deliverables are on strategy, client objectives are achieved and we are effectively communicating design decisions and course corrections to all stakeholders.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
Qualifications:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Professional experience and/or academic training in user-centered and strategic design methods as well as core management principles of marketing, organizational behavior and strategy</li>
<li>
Minimum 5+ years experience in a design or business consultancy</li>
</ul>
