&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Manage interdisciplinary teams of visual designers, writers, interaction designers, and programmers helping to evolve creative concepts into clear sets of deliverables in a way that balances client requirements with team growth and morale<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Serve as the main client interface on projects, helping define vision, clarifying strategic requirements, explaining complex ideas clearly, and managing expectations<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Serve as primary day-to-day contact for clients<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Keep projects on track through clear task lists, issue tracking, status reports, and meeting notes<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Lead efficient meetings and conference calls with the ability to effectively setup the presentation of creative work<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Clearly communicate project issues and resolution to the client and internal team<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Play a dual role of client advocate and R/GA team advocate<br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Be passionate about delivering the best creative, but find ways of producing it that does not jeopardize schedule and budget</p>
