At R/GA the Planning director has to have a proven ability to work independently to grow a brand or business.&nbsp; Although you will report into a Global Head of Planning you will be accountable for their specific brand or business and as such will require strong management and leadership skills.&nbsp; You should be able to demonstrate the ability to lead clients to difficult or new strategic areas and crafting strong strategic arguments support for their recommendations.&nbsp; You should be able to show strong management with a multi-disciplinary team and with younger planners.&nbsp;<br />
&nbsp;<br />
A planning director should have solid craft skills in all core areas of planning from research and insights, business strategy, media and connections, analytics, cultural trends digital and social strategies.<br />
&nbsp;<br />
