Group Planning Director:</p>
<p>
Group planning director is our most senior planning role.&nbsp; GPD&rsquo;s are responsible for overseeing the strategic future of a group of clients, one of our global brands or one of our larger multi-business clients.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p>
As one of our most senior strategic leads the GPD is expected to be both a strong manager and thought leader in the planning discipline. They should be pioneering new ways of thinking for our clients and for the industry at large.&nbsp; They are expected to push forward the strategic reputation of the agency in both the eyes of our clients, the industry and with the executive management of the agency.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
GPD candidates should have a proven history of industry leading strategy and creative work.&nbsp;&nbsp; They should have a proven history of managing a senior team of planners and strategists. They will have independent responsibility for building and growing the planning discipline across their group of accounts and will partner with the leadership team of other R/GA disciplines to take responsibility for the growth and development of R/GA&rsquo;s business.&nbsp; They should have a broad experience of many different strategic disciplines and categories.&nbsp; They should exemplify the highest possible standard of craft skills that are required in a senior strategist in the digital age.</p>
