&nbsp;<br />
<strong>Planning Director</strong><br />
<strong>&nbsp;</strong><br />
A Planning Director is the strategic leader on a specific business.&nbsp;&nbsp; As the strategic leader you will be responsible for partnering with other leaders on the account to guide our most senior clients to bold and innovative solutions.&nbsp; In this role we expect a proven track record of success at leading industry or innovative strategies.&nbsp; You will be expected to demonstrate the highest standard of business and audience analysis that will lead to business growing solutions.&nbsp; You will also be expected to have a history of translating these discoveries into inspiring briefs and roadmaps for the brand.&nbsp; You will also be expected to work with creative, production and account partners to sell these innovative strategies to client and to industry leading creative work.&nbsp;<br />
&nbsp;<br />
At R/GA the Planning director has to have a proven ability to work independently to grow a brand or business.&nbsp; Although you will report into a Head of Planning you will be accountable for their specific brand or business and as such will require strong management and leadership skills.&nbsp; You should be able to demonstrate the ability to lead clients to difficult or new strategic areas and crafting strong strategic arguments support for their recommendations.&nbsp; You should be able to show strong management with a multi-disciplinary team and with younger planners.&nbsp;<br />
&nbsp;<br />
A planning director should have solid craft skills in all core areas of planning from research and insights, business strategy, media and connections, analytics, cultural trends digital and social strategies.<br />
&nbsp;<br />
&nbsp;</p>
