			<description><![CDATA[<p>
A Senior Producer leads large interactive projects and is responsible for their success. At R/GA, success is defined not only as on time and on budget, but meeting client business requirements in a way that demonstrates creativity. A Senior Producer manages not only creative and development project teams, but other producers supporting specific projects.</p>
<p>
Responsibilities</p>
<p>
&bull; Lead discovery process on large engagements and accurately scope projects, defining project requirements and success metrics<br />
&bull; Manage multi-million dollar projects or multiple projects that total over a million dollars<br />
&bull; Serve as the main client interface on projects, clarify strategic requirements, explain complex ideas clearly, and manage expectations<br />
&bull; Oversee multiple producers and interdisciplinary project teams as large as 15 people<br />
&bull; Lead and inspire teams by communicating a vision for the project as well as involving people at the optimal levels for project success and overall account utilization<br />
&bull; Lead meetings with senior clients, ensure that they meet the stated objectives and stay on agenda<br />
&bull; Ensure all deliverables are of the highest quality<br />
&bull; Work in an independent fashion, solve problems, make decisions, and communicate effectively in difficult situations<br />
&bull; Be a passionate about delivering the best creative, but find ways of producing it that does not jeopardize schedule and budget<br />
&bull; Play a dual role of client advocate and R/GA team advocate<br />
&bull; Assist in training of producers and associate producers on R/GA methodology and PM skills<br />
&bull; Participate in the development of new business</p>
<p>
Knowledge / Experience / Ability</p>
<p>
&bull; Prior experience as an interactive producer/project manager<br />
&bull; Demonstrated experience running large engagements with Fortune 500 clients or equivalent experience<br />
&bull; Effective presentation and communication skills as evidenced by ability to develop presentations and speak to large audiences including senior level clients.<br />
&bull; Excellent negotiation skills, including Statement of Work<br />
&bull; Experience scoping large engagement, with development of project plans in MS Project<br />
&bull; Management of projects that exceed $500,000 in budget that met with business requirements and were on schedule and budget<br />
&bull; Familiarity with various project types, including: web sites, online advertising, campaigns, kiosks, mobile, signage, brand, and consulting.<br />
&bull; Strong knowledge of web development technologies. Knowledge of quality assurance process is required.<br />
&bull; Bachelor&#39;s degree or equivalent required. PMI certification a plus.</p>
