They must demonstrate that they have successfully taken their strategic work to near-full execution and have proven success at delivering strategically driven creative work.&nbsp; Senior brand strategist must also demonstrate solid craft and skill in all core areas of strategy from research and insights, business strategy, innovation, cultural trends, digital and social strategies.</p>
<p>
Their mindset should be creative in the way they think. They should embrace ambiguity and open-ended problems and come up with fresh approaches to solve for them.&nbsp; And they should have a love for and appreciation of beautiful design.</p>
<p>
Vision: Fundamentally passionate about the role of brand development in driving business and innovation across products, services and communications. Innately curious about the world of brand and business and have a deep understanding for how technology is changing the role of brands in consumer&rsquo;s day-to-day lives.</p>
<p>
Leadership: Pro-active, take charge leader with proven strategic vision; can manage, motivate, challenge, empower and delegate to others while leading by example; gains the trust of other parties quickly. Possesses the wisdom and confidence to take educated risks. Has ability to see both the bigger picture but not be afraid of getting involved in the detail when necessary. Is sought out by others for strategic advice and counsel.</p>
<p>
Curiosity/Creativity: An innovative and resourceful person who thinks and acts &ldquo;outside-of-the-box.&rdquo; This individual possesses a left brain/right brain mindset. Has a naturally curious mind, loves to explore and nurture intellect; knows how to observe and identify patterns that identify trends and key insights early; knows how to ask the right questions (relevant) and quantity of questions necessary to uncover key information that can be made actionable. Ideally an avid observer and follower of popular culture and societal trends.</p>
<p>
Technology Forward: Has a passion for technology, tinkering under the hood, and enjoys being a sought after authority and the resource that others turn to for emerging media.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
Responsibilities<br />
&bull; Use a variety of research methods (primary and secondary) uncover insights that inform and inspire a brand&rsquo;s positioning and expression<br />
&bull; Articulate brand concepts (narrative, positioning, personality etc.) clearly and concisely in written form and visually (working together with designers)<br />
&bull; Work in an integrated capacity with visual designers, experience designers and copy writers to ensure that deliverable is brought to life in a way that is engaging, impressive and true to strategic intent<br />
&bull; Analyze, comprehend and synthesize business documentation/research and its assess its impact on brand<br />
&bull; Structure and participate in qualitative research including stakeholder interviews, ethnographic research, contextual interviews and other forms of research techniques<br />
&bull; Design and execute client workshops with a wide range of clients (junior and senior)&mdash;this includes planning agendas, facilitating workshop, driving the creation of stimulus and activities and authoring report-backs to client and ensuring that output is used in strategy and design deliverables<br />
&bull; Confidently present and defend POVs and strategies to senior executives<br />
&bull; Understand and distill complex ideas into clear and understandable narratives that clarify problems and offer solutions built off of insights<br />
&bull; Ensuring the quality and best practices of the strategic thinking and proposals produced by R/GA is of the highest standard and commensurate with R/GA reputation for breakthrough interactive solutions.<br />
&bull; Sharing responsibility with other team managers for &lsquo;flawless execution&rsquo; of all client deliverables<br />
&bull; Build strong relationships with multiple levels of clients</p>
<p>
<br />
Requirements &amp; Qualifications</p>
<p>
&bull; Proven track record of developing brand strategies, positioning brands, creating brand architectures, and innovating products, services or experiences<br />
&bull; 3-5 years of experience at a brand, innovation, or design consultancy working with developing insights, leading cultural trends, inspiring and driving big ideas<br />
&bull; Strong writing skills in both strategic and creative capacities<br />
&bull; Deep understanding of and passion for the impact of technology on culture and behavior<br />
&bull; Experience working with syndicated research and ability to lead the design for primary research in both quantitative and qualitative techniques. In addition experience with specialized research practices for interactive/digital space (such as ethnography, one-on-one interviews, cultural anthropology, and usability)<br />
&bull; Solid quantitative and qualitative analytical skills<br />
&bull; Aptitude and cultural fit to inspire and collaborate with interaction/interface designers as well as the art and copy side of creative</p>
]]></description>
